A father who has allegedly snatched his two young children from a hotel where they were staying with their mother is being urged to contact police over concerns for the youngsters' welfare.

Saleem Tahir, 40, was believed to have forced his way into the hotel room and grabbed his two-and-a-half year old daughter Na'llah Khan and her brother, 10-month-old Sulailman Khan.

The young siblings had been in their mother's care at a hotel in the Hanley area of Stoke-on-Trent, Staffordshire, when they were taken at around 5pm on Friday, according to Nottinghamshire Police.

